HEADWORD: Tig
<hw>Tig</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A game among
children. See <er>Tag</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A capacious, flat-bottomed drinking cup, generally
with four handles, formerly used for passing around the table at
convivial entertainment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tigella</ent>⟦br⟧
